      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm working on this embedded c++ project for an automotive sensor module and we're seeing a slow memory leak in the telemetry loop. it takes about 4-6 hours of operation before the heap is totally exhausted. i think it might be in the data processing stage but i can't pin it down. \n\ncan u look at this snippet and suggest a systematic way to find where the leak is happening?\n\n```cpp\nvoid process_sensor_data(const uint8_t* buffer, size_t len) {\n    // Allocate buffer for processed packet\n    uint8_t* processed_packet = new uint8_t[len];\n    \n    // copy data\n    std::memcpy(processed_packet, buffer, len);\n    \n    // perform some transform logic\n    apply_calibration(processed_packet, len);\n    \n    // dispatch to telemetry queue\n    if (telemetry_queue.push(processed_packet)) {\n        // success\n    } else {\n        // if queue is full, we need to handle it\n        log_error(\"queue full\");\n        // TODO: handle failure\n    }\n}\n```\nit's a critical system so i need a real debugging strategy, not just a guess.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
